<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF70FB68FEFCFB32" blockId="4.[151,723,1158,1221]" box="[151,284,1195,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFF70FB68FEFCFB32" box="[151,284,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figs. 32–34</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF70FB30FCD5FA8E" blockId="4.[151,1437,1267,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<collectingCounty id="62A8E994FFBCFF9BFF70FB30FF31FAFA" box="[151,209,1267,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Most</collectingCounty>
specimens of 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BAD0B62FFBCFF9BFE93FB30FDDDFAFA" box="[372,573,1267,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Auchenorrhyncha</collectingMunicipality>
investigated by Prof. Zakhvatkin are deposited in the collection of the 
<location id="8EA9C7C3FFBCFF9BFA81FB30FEACFAC6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DF200EFFBCFF9AFF70FB45FB03FEB6:8EA9C7C3FFBCFF9BFA81FB30FEACFAC6" county="Most" municipality="Auchenorrhyncha" name="Zoological Museum" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" stateProvince="Moscow">Zoological Museum</location>
of 
<collectingRegion id="49B25FFAFFBCFF9BFE97FAD4FDEFFAC6" box="[368,527,1303,1329]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Moscow State</collectingRegion>
University. However, 
<typeStatus id="54CD2FBAFFBCFF9BFCECFAD4FCDBFAC6" box="[779,827,1303,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
specimens of a considerable number of his species are absent in the collection, and male specimens usually lack genital segments. For this reason, we found it useful to provide information about the 
<typeStatus id="54CD2FBAFFBCFF9BFE0AFA9CFDFDFA8E" box="[493,541,1375,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFD6DFA9CFCCFFA8E" baseAuthorityName="Zakhvatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1953" box="[650,815,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elpatjevskii">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFD6DFA9CFCCFFA8E" box="[650,815,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">M. elpatjevskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF20FA40FC71F9A6" blockId="4.[151,1437,1267,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
The original description (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFE0EFA40FD54FA6A" author="Zakhvatkin, A. A." box="[489,692,1410,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" pagination="247 - 250" refId="ref4242" refString="Zakhvatkin, A. A. (1953) Auchenorrhyncha, collected by V. S. Elpatyevskiy on the shores of the Khubsugul Lake (former Kosogol). In: Smirnov, E. S. (Ed.), Sbornik nauchnykh rabot. Moscow University, Moscow, pp. 247 - 250. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1953">Zakhvatkin, 1953</bibRefCitation>
) is based on 
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFBCFF9BFCA8FA40FC23FA6A" box="[847,963,1411,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFBCFF9BFC18FA40FB6DFA6A" box="[1023,1165,1411,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
. All 
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFBCFF9BFB23FA40FA91FA6A" box="[1220,1393,1411,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
are present in the collection, among them 
<materialsCitation id="3B1E9B45FFBCFF9BFDACFA64FB12F9FE" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3757431303" collectionCode="V, R" collectorName="V.S. Elpatyevsky" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-female="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="54CD2FBAFFBCFF9BFDACFA64FD50FA36" box="[587,688,1447,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFBCFF9BFD5AFA64FD32FA36" box="[701,722,1447,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFD05FA64FCD7FA36" box="[738,823,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
), with labels: “L. [Lake] Kosogol [misspelled “Khubsugul”], 
<collectionCode id="ED6709DDFFBCFF9BFF10FA08FEEEFA12" box="[247,270,1483,1509]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. 
<collectorName id="2683F4CEFFBCFF9BFEF5FA08FE55FA12" box="[274,437,1482,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">S. Elpatyevsk</collectorName>
[y].”, “Mth. [Mouth] 
<collectionCode id="ED6709DDFFBCFF9BFD70FA08FD4DFA12" box="[663,685,1483,1509]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">R</collectionCode>
. [of the River] Khabtsyl, 5. VIII. [19]03” (in Russian, comments in square brackets), “Cotypus”, and “Delt. sp. nov. prop. bellevoyei Put. A. 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFC2AFA2CFBABF9FE" authority="Tishechkin, 2022" authorityName="Tishechkin" authorityYear="2022" box="[973,1099,1519,1545]" genus="Zachvatkin" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" rank="genus" status="g. n.">Zachvatkin</taxonomicName>
det.” (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFB7FFA2CFB0AF9FE" box="[1176,1258,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B1E9B45FFBCFF9BFB1DFA2CFCBBF9DA" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3757431307" collectionCode="V, R" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" specimenCount="7" specimenCount-female="3" specimenCount-male="3" typeStatus="holotype">
and 
<typeStatus id="54CD2FBAFFBCFF9BFACDFA2CFA78F9FE" box="[1322,1432,1519,1545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">paratypes</typeStatus>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFBCFF9BFF70F9D0FF24F9DA" box="[151,196,1555,1581]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="male">2 ♂</specimenCount>
, both dissected, genitalia preparations are absent (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFD1DF9D0FCAEF9DA" box="[762,846,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
),
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B1E9B45FFBCFF9BFC85F9D0FC6CF9A6" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3757431304" collectionCode="V, R" collectorName="L. Kosogol &amp; S. Elpatyevsky" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" specimenCount="7" specimenCount-female="3" specimenCount-male="3" typeStatus="holotype">
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFBCFF9BFC85F9D0FC6DF9DA" box="[866,909,1555,1581]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
with only two first labels same as in 
<typeStatus id="54CD2FBAFFBCFF9BFAD4F9D0FA78F9DA" box="[1331,1432,1555,1581]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">holotype</typeStatus>
, “ 
<collectorName id="2683F4CEFFBCFF9BFF44F9F4FEC5F9A6" box="[163,293,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">L. Kosogol</collectorName>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED6709DDFFBCFF9BFEC8F9F4FEA6F9A6" box="[303,326,1591,1617]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. 
<collectorName id="2683F4CEFFBCFF9BFEADF9F4FE0BF9A6" box="[330,491,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">S. Elpatyevsk.</collectorName>
” and “Mth. 
<collectionCode id="ED6709DDFFBCFF9BFD93F9F4FD6AF9A6" box="[628,650,1591,1617]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">R</collectionCode>
. Khabtsyl, 5. VIII. 03”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF20F998FCC5F96E" blockId="4.[151,1437,1267,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
This species is similar in appearance to other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFCC9F998FC38F982" authorityName="Zakhvatkin" authorityYear="1953" box="[814,984,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFCC9F998FC38F982" box="[814,984,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFC01F998FB8CF982" box="[998,1132,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figs. 32, 34</figureCitation>
). Drawings of the aedeagus were published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFE8CF9BCFDDCF96E" author="Zakhvatkin, A. A." box="[363,572,1662,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" pagination="247 - 250" refId="ref4242" refString="Zakhvatkin, A. A. (1953) Auchenorrhyncha, collected by V. S. Elpatyevskiy on the shores of the Khubsugul Lake (former Kosogol). In: Smirnov, E. S. (Ed.), Sbornik nauchnykh rabot. Moscow University, Moscow, pp. 247 - 250. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1953">Zakhvatkin (1953)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFD94F9BCFCC1F96E" author="Dlabola, J." box="[627,801,1662,1689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" pagination="79 - 136" refId="ref3467" refString="Dlabola, J. (1965) Ergebnisse der zoologischen Forschungen von Dr. Z. Kaszab in der Mongolei. 54. Homoptera - Auchenorrhyncha. Acta faunistica entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 11 (100), 79 - 136." type="journal article" year="1965">Dlabola (1965)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF20F960FC0BF8DE" blockId="4.[151,1437,1267,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
The description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFE78F960FDA6F94A" baseAuthorityName="Zakhvatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1953" box="[415,582,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elpatjevskii">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFE78F960FDA6F94A" box="[415,582,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">M. elpatjevskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published after the death of Prof. Zakhvatkin in a collection of works, the manuscripts of which, in a more or less finished form, were found in his archive. For this reason, some works contain omissions or inaccuracies. In particular, in the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFC68F928FBD3F8F2" baseAuthorityName="Zakhvatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1953" box="[911,1075,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elpatjevskii">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFC68F928FBD3F8F2" box="[911,1075,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">M. elpatjevskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is a contradiction concerning the generic placement of this species. The description begins as follows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF70F8F0FD5FF8BA" blockId="4.[151,1437,1267,2013]" box="[151,703,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
“ 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFF43F8F0FD95F8BA" authority="A. Zachvatkin" authorityName="A. Zachvatkin" authorityYear="2022" box="[164,629,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elpatjevskii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFF43F8F0FE2CF8BA" box="[164,460,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Deltocephalus elpatjevskii</emphasis>
A. Zachvatkin
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFD98F8F0FD5FF8BA" bold="true" box="[639,703,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A231F071FFBCFF9BFD98F8F0FD5FF8BA" box="[639,703,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF70F894FC95F886" blockId="4.[151,1437,1267,2013]" box="[151,885,1878,1907]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
— 
<materialsCitation id="3B1E9B45FFBCFF9BFF53F894FC91F886" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3757431306" box="[180,881,1878,1907]" location="The" municipality="Khabtsyl River" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" specimenCount="4" specimenCount-female="2" specimenCount-male="2">
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFBCFF9BFF53F894FF16F884" box="[180,246,1879,1907]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="male">2 ♂♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D705A91FFBCFF9BFEE7F894FEDFF886" box="[256,319,1879,1905]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="female">2 ♀♀</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFEA8F894FE74F886" box="[335,404,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-16@2.[194,1393,179,1872]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Mongolojassus caucasicus sp. n. (1–14) and M. servadeinus (15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). 
<location id="8EA9C7C3FFBCFF9BFE4FF894FE34F886" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DF200EFFBCFF9AFF70FB45FB03FEB6:8EA9C7C3FFBCFF9BFE4FF894FE34F886" box="[424,468,1879,1905]" municipality="Khabtsyl River" name="The" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">The</location>
mouth of the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BAD0B62FFBCFF9BFD97F894FCFCF886" box="[624,796,1879,1905]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Khabtsyl River</collectingMunicipality>
, 5/VIII
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9AFF70F8B8FB03FEB6" blockId="4.[151,1437,1267,2013]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,150,321]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="579" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
Close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFF19F8B8FDECF862" authority="Horv. 1901" authorityName="Horv." authorityYear="1901" box="[254,524,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFF19F8B8FE62F862" box="[254,386,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">D. sibiricus</emphasis>
Horv. 1901
</taxonomicName>
, forming together with it a sharply separated association, belonging to the wellknown group “ocellati”, which, of course, can be separated as a special genus (
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFBEFF85CFAB9F84E" authority="A. Zachvatkin" authorityName="A. Zachvatkin" authorityYear="2022" box="[1032,1369,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="g. n.">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFBEFF85CFB52F84E" box="[1032,1202,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
A. Zachvatkin
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A231F071FFBCFF9BFA83F85CFA76F84E" box="[1380,1430,1951,1977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" rank="genus">g. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; typ. gen. 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFF1AF800FD6BF82A" authority="Horv. 1901" authorityName="Horv." authorityYear="1901" box="[253,651,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFF1AF800FDE4F82A" box="[253,516,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Deltocephalus sibiricus</emphasis>
Horv. 1901
</taxonomicName>
). Very similar in general appearance, 
<typeStatus id="54CD2FBAFFBCFF9BFBCEF800FBB9F82A" box="[1065,1113,1987,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
of coloration and anatomical features to 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBDFF9AFEF6FF54FE72FF46" box="[273,402,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBDFF9AFEF6FF54FE72FF46" box="[273,402,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="579">D. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only somewhat stouter and distinctly smaller [below, the description of the species follows]” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBDFF9AFF78FF78FE46FF22" author="Zakhvatkin, A. A." box="[159,422,186,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="579" pagination="247 - 250" refId="ref4242" refString="Zakhvatkin, A. A. (1953) Auchenorrhyncha, collected by V. S. Elpatyevskiy on the shores of the Khubsugul Lake (former Kosogol). In: Smirnov, E. S. (Ed.), Sbornik nauchnykh rabot. Moscow University, Moscow, pp. 247 - 250. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1953">Zakhvatkin, 1953: 249</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, this species was described in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBDFF9AFC2FFF78FAD8FF22" authority="Burmeister, 1838" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[968,1336,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBDFF9AFC2FFF78FB8AFF22" box="[968,1130,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="579">Deltocephalus</emphasis>
Burmeister, 1838
</taxonomicName>
, but was immediately attributed to the new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBDFF9AFD8EFF1CFCF3FF0E" authorityName="A. Zachvatkin" authorityYear="2022" box="[617,787,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBDFF9AFD8EFF1CFCF3FF0E" box="[617,787,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="579">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the same publication. Therefore, the original combination with 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBDFF9AFEE6FEC0FE43FEEA" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[257,419,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBDFF9AFEE6FEC0FE43FEEA" box="[257,419,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="579">Deltocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be considered a lapsus attributable to the unfinished nature of Zachvatkin’s manuscript, given the author’s clear intent to include both 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBDFF9AFD7CFEE4FCFDFEB6" box="[667,797,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBDFF9AFD7CFEE4FCFDFEB6" box="[667,797,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="579">D. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBDFF9AFC87FEE4FBE3FEB6" authorityName="A. Zachvatkin" authorityYear="2022" box="[864,1027,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elpatjevskii">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBDFF9AFC87FEE4FBE3FEB6" box="[864,1027,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="579">D. elpatjevskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBDFF9AFBD5FEE4FB3CFEB6" authorityName="A. Zachvatkin" authorityYear="2022" box="[1074,1244,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBDFF9AFBD5FEE4FB3CFEB6" box="[1074,1244,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="579">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
